<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,153,1403]" box="[199,1414,153,179]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Scutellum totally black, dull, scarcely raised, apex truncated in a straight line. Bald and devoid of punctures.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,153,1403]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Elytron surface black with two narrow, straight, longitudinal yellow stripes extending from anterior margin to apex where they coalesce, first one running along suture, second one on the middle of disc. Epipleuron and anterior half of elytral lateral margin yellow as well. Elytral outline parallel-sided and rather flattened on disc. Postscutellar area not raised. Humeral callus weakly developed, impunctate. Surface moderately matt with shallow, small, irregularly arranged punctation, only in posterior half of disc punctures arranged in rows. Intervals flat.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,153,1403]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Pygidium black with yellow transverse stripe in the middle, smooth, covered with sparse shallow punctures and whitish setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,153,1403]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Inferior parts of thorax totally black, only external part of hypomera partly yellow. Hypomera bare, rather deeply punctured, mesoepimera and mesoepisterna almost bare with scarce shallow punctures. Metaepisterna and metasternum with quite close, shallow punctation and sparse setae. Prosternal process coarsely punctured with long setae. Abdominal ventrites black with large yellow border, shallowly and sparsely punctured, with sparse setae. Legs totally black.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,153,1403]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">
Median depression on fifth abdominal ventrite moderately impressed, impunctate, almost bare. Posterior margin of fifth abdominal ventrite weakly notched. Median lobe of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[980,1058,657,683]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–13" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1822,1847]" captionTargetBox="[268,1284,194,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[214,1372,166,1802]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 12–13. M. octoguttatus (12), M. pollinctor (13). 12a–b: habitus; 12c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.7 mm]; 12f: sclerite I and dorsal spicule of endophallus [0.7 mm]; 12g: sclerites II–III–IV of endophallus [0.5 mm]; 12h: spermatheca [0.4 mm]; 12k: antenna [1.7 mm]. 13a–b: habitus; 13c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.8 mm]; 13f: sclerite I and dorsal spicule of endophallus [0.6 mm]; 13g: sclerites II–III–IV of endophallus [0.6 mm]; 13h: spermatheca [0.5 mm]; 13k: antenna [2.0 mm]. 12a–b: lectotype; 13a–b: lectotype. scI–IV: sclerites I–IV of endophallus; ds: dorsal spicule. Square brackets: length of scale segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3763891" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3763891/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
c–e) cylindrical with apex scarcely separated from the rest of aedeagus, blunt, in lateral view almost straight. Hairy dents moderately impressed, scarcely delimited, bearing rather long, dense setae. Aedeagal ventral surface barely swollen in lateral view, devoid of particular structures. Endophallus (
<figureCitation box="[574,652,765,792]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–13" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1822,1847]" captionTargetBox="[268,1284,194,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[214,1372,166,1802]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 12–13. M. octoguttatus (12), M. pollinctor (13). 12a–b: habitus; 12c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.7 mm]; 12f: sclerite I and dorsal spicule of endophallus [0.7 mm]; 12g: sclerites II–III–IV of endophallus [0.5 mm]; 12h: spermatheca [0.4 mm]; 12k: antenna [1.7 mm]. 13a–b: habitus; 13c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.8 mm]; 13f: sclerite I and dorsal spicule of endophallus [0.6 mm]; 13g: sclerites II–III–IV of endophallus [0.6 mm]; 13h: spermatheca [0.5 mm]; 13k: antenna [2.0 mm]. 12a–b: lectotype; 13a–b: lectotype. scI–IV: sclerites I–IV of endophallus; ds: dorsal spicule. Square brackets: length of scale segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3763891" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3763891/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
f–g) with sclerite I strongly developed and pigmented, denticle apparent, rather pointed, bent upwards and not perceptibly sticking out laterally. Dorsal spicule long, thorn-like. Sclerite II long, robust, distinctly bent at base and gradually tapered towards apex. Arch of sclerite III slender, raised. Apex of sclerite III straight, slender and pointed distally, fairly expanded on its proximal half, so that the sclerite looks like the head of a grebe. Branches of sclerite IV shorter than sclerite III in the folded-up structure, slightly arched towards ventral direction, with blunt, almost symmetrical, microdenticulate apex and surface perceptibly rugose.
</paragraph>
