, PL = 
<quantity box="[760,849,980,1007]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
, PW = 
<quantity box="[936,1027,981,1007]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
. Interocular distance 11.5–13.2% of BL.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,153,1403]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">
Fifth abdominal ventrite in females with quite large, rather deep, almost circular pit. Bottom of pit bald, matt, impunctate but covered with tiny wrinkles. Vasculum of spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[954,1051,1089,1116]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–13" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1822,1847]" captionTargetBox="[268,1284,194,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[214,1372,166,1802]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 12–13. M. octoguttatus (12), M. pollinctor (13). 12a–b: habitus; 12c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.7 mm]; 12f: sclerite I and dorsal spicule of endophallus [0.7 mm]; 12g: sclerites II–III–IV of endophallus [0.5 mm]; 12h: spermatheca [0.4 mm]; 12k: antenna [1.7 mm]. 13a–b: habitus; 13c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.8 mm]; 13f: sclerite I and dorsal spicule of endophallus [0.6 mm]; 13g: sclerites II–III–IV of endophallus [0.6 mm]; 13h: spermatheca [0.5 mm]; 13k: antenna [2.0 mm]. 12a–b: lectotype; 13a–b: lectotype. scI–IV: sclerites I–IV of endophallus; ds: dorsal spicule. Square brackets: length of scale segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3763891" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3763891/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Fig. 13h</figureCitation>
) scarcely pigmented with straight proximal branch not swollen at base, long distal branch and very short, pointed, straight apex. Ampulla strongly pigmented, slightly shifted on dorsal side of vasculum. Duct and sperm gland insertions clearly distinct. Duct uniform in size, rather robust, remarkably short, coiled with coils markedly loose and irregularly arranged, more resembling wavings than true coils. Distal not coiled portion of duct long, straight. Insertion on bursa copulatrix lengthened, almost straight, moderately pigmented.
</paragraph>
